PUH-BrianMartell E8 Roots to SM Multiplets Mapping — Understandable Explanation The Standard Model has particles in specific multiplets: quarks in color triplets (3) and weak doublets (2), leptons in singlets (1) and doublets (2), three generations. In PUH v25, E8 roots (240 minimal twist directions) project onto lower-dimensional subspaces to classify these multiplets. Simple picture: •  E8 roots = basis for all possible stable twists. •  Projection onto SU(3)_c color subspace → multiplicity 3 (triplets for quarks) or 1 (singlets for leptons). •  Projection onto SU(2)_L weak subspace → doublets (2) or singlets (1). •  Hypercharge from combined projection. •  Generations from three hierarchical nested projections (increasing internal frustration → mass hierarchy). •  Right-handed neutrinos from singlet projections. No arbitrary assignment — multiplets emerge from E8 root decomposition under projection subgroups.
